<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Dikmer on 04-20-2001 01:29 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well, I bound myself next to the forge in Freeport, bought molds, ran to HK, bought the ore, made armor til I ran out of molds, then made MQ Sheet metal till I was full and gated back to where the molds could be bought.

So you really only have to run one way.

My problem now, is I am broke, and have 2 full sets of FP armor and cant seem to sell it. Had someone in GFay today who kinda pissed me off. I was asking 1500pp for a full (visual) set of BP, Helm, Arms, Gloves, Legs, Boots and 2 Bracers. I felt that was fair. 

She started complaining that she could buy dyed for 1500pp, so I dropped to 1250 (I need the cash to make more armor). THEN she startd asking where the "rest of the full set" is. I.E. she expected a visor, pauldron, cloak and belt to be included.

Quick math. 7.5pp per brick of MQ ore, 3 to make a MQ folded sheet. 22.5pp per sheet. Takes 25 sheets to make a "FULL" set. 562.5pp assuming NO fails. Molds average 15pp each (some higher, some lower), 12 molds total. 180pp. So, not counting pads, 750pp per set with ZERO fails. I have been getting 50-60% success, so my COST is 1300pp. And she expected me to sell at a loss. Her reasoning? "Thats the cost of being a smith". 

Why the heck would anyone become a smith if everyone expects you to sell at a loss.

I am half considering just selling FSPlate to vendors and hunting Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains to fund it.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
